# `solace.service.j2` — Dual Runtime Logic (`podman run` vs `podman-compose`)

## Overview

The `solace.service.j2` systemd unit template supports **two mutually exclusive container runtimes** in a single file, controlled by the Ansible variable `broker_runtime`.

| `broker_runtime` value | Runtime used |
|---|---|
| `podman_compose` | `podman-compose` (foreground, `Type=simple`) |
| *(anything else / not set)* | `podman run` (default, `Type=notify`) |

The shared sections (unit dependencies, environment variable declarations, restart policy, etc.) remain **identical for both runtimes** — only the `[Service]` execution block differs.

---

## Template Branch Structure

```
solace.service.j2
│
├── [Unit] section          ← shared (same for both runtimes)
├── [Install] section       ← shared
├── [Service] — common      ← shared (EnvironmentFile, Environment=PSP_*, Restart=always, TimeoutStartSec)
│
└── {% if broker_runtime | default('systemd') == 'podman_compose' %}
    │
    ├── podman-compose path  ← Type=simple, ExecStart=podman-compose up
    │
    {% else %}
    │
    └── podman run path      ← Type=notify, ExecStart=podman run … ${PSP_IMAGE}
    │
    {% endif %}
```

---

## Shared Section (before the branch)

Everything from `[Unit]` through the `Environment=PSP_*` defaults and `Restart=always` is **common to both runtimes**.

Key shared items:
- `EnvironmentFile` — loads `solace.conf` and `solace-user.conf`
- `Environment=PSP_*` — all port/mount/credential variables are pre-defaulted to a harmless dummy value so systemd does not choke if a variable is missing
- `Restart=always`
- `TimeoutStartSec={{ broker.systemd_timeout_start | default(300) }}`

---

## Branch 1 — `podman-compose` path

**Condition:** `broker_runtime == 'podman_compose'`

```ini
Environment=XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/%U
Type=simple
WorkingDirectory=/home/<solace_user>/solace

ExecStartPre=-<podman-compose-bin> -f <compose-file> down --timeout 60
ExecStart=<podman-compose-bin>  -f <compose-file> up
ExecStop=<podman-compose-bin>   -f <compose-file> down --timeout 120
TimeoutStopSec=180
```

### Key points
| Property | Value / Reason |
|---|---|
| `Type=simple` | `podman-compose up` runs in the foreground; systemd considers the service started immediately |
| `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` | Required by rootless Podman inside a systemd unit |
| `WorkingDirectory` | Set to the compose file's directory so relative paths resolve correctly |
| `ExecStartPre` (with `-`) | Attempts a `down` before starting; the leading `-` makes failure non-fatal |
| `TimeoutStopSec` | 180 s — allows the `down --timeout 120` to complete |
| `solace_compose_bin` | Defaults to `/home/<user>/.local/bin/podman-compose` |
| `solace_compose_file` | Defaults to `/home/<user>/solace/solace-compose.yml` |

