## Branch 2 — `podman run` path (default)

**Condition:** `broker_runtime` is **not** `podman_compose` (or not set at all)

```ini
TimeoutStopSec=1260
Type=notify
NotifyAccess=all
Delegate=yes

ExecStartPre=/bin/bash -c 'echo PSP_USER_ID=$(id -u <user>) > .../solace-user.conf'
ExecStart=/usr/bin/podman run \
  --env-file=.../solace.env \
  --user ${PSP_USER_ID} \
  --cidfile=%t/%N.cid \
  ${PSP_COMMON_ARGS_*} \
  ${PSP_*} \         ← all port / mount / credential args
  ${PSP_IMAGE}

ExecStop=/usr/bin/podman stop <container> --time 1200
ExecStopPost=-/usr/bin/podman rm -f -i --cidfile=%t/%N.cid
ExecStopPost=-rm -f %t/%N.cid
```

### Key points
| Property | Value / Reason |
|---|---|
| `Type=notify` | Podman sends `sd_notify` when the container is ready; more reliable health signalling |
| `Delegate=yes` | Hands cgroup management to Podman |
| `TimeoutStopSec=1260` | Intentionally > the `podman stop --time 1200` (1200 s) to avoid systemd killing the stop command early |
| `ExecStartPre` | Writes the UID of `solace_local_service_user` into `solace-user.conf` so `--user ${PSP_USER_ID}` works at runtime |
| `ExecStopPost` | Two-step cleanup: remove the container, then remove the `.cid` file; leading `-` makes each step non-fatal |
| `PSP_*` variables | Sourced from `solace.conf`; the template-level defaults prevent systemd parse errors if any variable is absent |

