## Variable Reference

| Ansible Variable | Default | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `broker_runtime` | `'systemd'` (triggers `podman run` branch) | Selects which runtime branch to render |
| `solace_compose_bin` | `/home/<user>/.local/bin/podman-compose` | Path to `podman-compose` binary |
| `solace_compose_file` | `/home/<user>/solace/solace-compose.yml` | Path to the compose file |
| `solace_container_name` | *(required for podman run)* | Name passed to `podman stop` |
| `solace_local_service_user` | *(required)* | Rootless user owning the container |
| `broker.systemd_timeout_start` | `300` | `TimeoutStartSec` value |

---

## Why a Single Template?

- **DRY** — all shared environment variable defaults, mount requirements, and restart policies live in one place.
- **Consistency** — any change to the `[Unit]` or shared `[Service]` properties automatically applies to both runtimes.
- **Simple onboarding** — operators only need to set `broker_runtime: podman_compose` (or leave it unset) in their inventory/host_vars; no separate template to maintain.

---

## Decision Flow

```
         ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
         │  broker_runtime is defined and == 'podman_compose'?  │
         └────────────────────┬─────────────────────────┘
                    YES       │        NO (default)
             ┌────────────────┘         └────────────────┐
             ▼                                           ▼
   podman-compose branch                       podman run branch
   Type=simple                                 Type=notify
   ExecStart: podman-compose up                ExecStart: podman run … ${PSP_IMAGE}
   TimeoutStopSec=180                          TimeoutStopSec=1260
```

